What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Flaxseed Oil Market?



Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Flaxseed Oil Market

The flaxseed oil market is expected to be growing at a growth rate of 3.5% in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. The growing utilization in most of industrial applications of flaxseed oil in urban areas will act as a driving factor to the growth of the flaxseed oil market.

Flax seed, which is also known as linseed which are a rich source of nutritional benefits such as vitamin B1, dietary fiber, magnesium, zinc, lignans and essential fatty acids. Flax seeds are best identified for its culinary uses and health benefits. Flax seeds oil is an eatable oil and has been used for thousands of years. It has been one of the most needed edible oils across the world.

Major factors that are expected to boost the growth of the flaxseed oil market in the forecast period are the rise in the alertness concerning the health advantages of Flax seed like helping with the weight reduction, stimulating the systolic and diastolic blood pressure and enhancing the hair density and length and so forth. The upsurge in the demand for flaxseed oil in the advanced and developing countries and the increase in the utilization in various application in the automobile and consumer goods industry will is further anticipated to propel the growth of the flaxseed oil market.

On the other hand, the side effects caused by the flaxseed oil such as skin irritation and eye redness to infants when present in the childcare products and the variations in the costs of the raw materials are few of the other factors further estimated to obstruct the growth of the flaxseed oil market in the near future.

